</div>
<div class="text uiwText parbase section">








   


 









 


 


   
    <!-- 
    **note changes made above in normal non preview css styles
    repeat the style writing above and append X at the end of the component id for preview
     --> 
   
    
    <div id="toolbarObj244296099" class="allToolbarSelector"></div>
    
    
    
    
<script>                                                       

</script>
<div id="component244296099" class="textComponent">  

<div class="text"><p><a href="/content/dam/humanrights/what-to-expect/complaint-process/DHP-Infographic-Final.pdf" target="_blank">Download Complaint Process</a><br>
</p>
<h3>Description</h3>
<p><strong>Does the DHP apply to your issue?</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>No, then Human Rights Services will make appropriate referrals.</li>
<li>Yes, then you may engage the human rights process at Ryerson.</li>
</ul>
<ol>
<li><strong>Intakes:&nbsp;</strong>The Complainant shares concerns with Human Rights Services, describes what happened and who is involved. Formal investigation process &amp; alternative options are discussed. Complaints can include systemic issues related to policies and procedures.</li>
<li><strong><strong>Alternative Resolutions:</strong></strong><ul>
<li><strong>Consultation or Coaching:</strong> Human Rights Services will support you in resolving the issue independently.</li>
<li><strong>Conciliation:</strong> If the Complainant and Respondent are willing, Human Rights Services can mediate a resolution. If successful, both parties sign a written record of resolution.<ul>
<li><strong>Resolution: </strong>The issue might be resolved at this point.</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><strong>Complaint Process:</strong> If the matter is not resolved through the Alternative Resolution process or if the Complainant prefers to submit a complaint, they can. This can happen at any time during the Alternative Resolution process.</li>
<li><strong>Complaint: </strong>The Complainant prepares and submits a signed letter of complaint to Human Rights Services along with any supporting documentation and names of witnesses, if applicable.</li>
<li><strong>Decision Maker</strong>: Human Rights Services identifies a senior administrator as decision-maker.</li>
<li><strong>Investigation: </strong>An Investigator will be assigned to investigate the complaint. The Investigator works independently to analyze the complaint and write a report on their findings, including:<ul>
<li>Interviewing complainants, respondents and witnesses</li>
<li>Reviewing any documentation</li>
<li>Allowing the Complainant and Respondent to review and respond to a summary of their statements.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><strong>Case Analysis: </strong>The Investigator documents their findings in a Case Analysis Report and presents the findings to the Complainant and Respondent. The Investigator will then forward the Case Analysis to the senior administrator for a decision.</li>
<li><strong>Decision</strong>: The decision-maker reviews the report and has the opportunity to meet with all parties and university administrators as required. The decision-maker renders a decision and where applicable, assigns sanctions/remedies.</li>
<li><strong>Remedy</strong></li>
<li><strong>Appeal Process: </strong>Parties can appeal based on matters of substance and/or process.</li>
</ol>
<div><strong><p>Support is available throughout this process</p>
</strong><br>
</div></div>

<div style="clear:both;"></div>
</div>     
   












</div>
<div class="text uiwText parbase section">








   


 









 


 


   
    <!-- 
    **note changes made above in normal non preview css styles
    repeat the style writing above and append X at the end of the component id for preview
